    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/7"
                        key="#Emperor/king #Imperial/royal_diploma">Otto</persName> tercius secundum voluntatem Iesu
                        Christi Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus
                        sanctarumque ecclesiarum devotissimus et fidelissimus dilatator. Notum sit
                        omnibus fidelibus nostris, qualiter <rs key="#Intercessory">interventu et peticione</rs> <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Intercessory" ref="#people/3">Vgonis </persName><rs
                            key="#Marquis/duke">marchionis</rs> nostri dilectissimi fidelis <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">dedimus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mother_churches"><orgName ref="#juridical_persons/81"
                                key="#Mother_churches">sancto Eusebio</orgName></rs> cui dominus
                            <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/171">Leo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> preesse videtur, duas <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >cortes</rs> iuris nostri <geogName ref="#estates/205"
                            key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Aldius #Slave"
                                ><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Aldius #Slave"
                                ref="#places/212">Clauaziam</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Aldius #Slave"
                            ref="#estates/206"><placeName ref="#places/457"
                                key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Aldius #Slave"
                                >Bedolium</placeName></geogName> in integrum cum omnibus terris
                        massariciis <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs> pratis pascuis vineis <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscacionibus</rs> venacionibus <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripis aquis aquarumque
                            decursibus </rs><rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> omnibusque terris
                        cultis et incultis, cum omnibus <rs key="#Slave">servis</rs> et ancillis <rs
                            key="#Aldius">aldionibus</rs> et aldiabus et cum omnibus rebus mobilibus
                        et inmobilibus ad easdem cortes in integrum pertinentibus et cum omnibus que
                        dici possunt ad easdem cortes respicientibus, ut tam Leo episcopus quam
                        omnes sui successores habeant teneant ordinent et quodcumque velint faciant,
                        salva tantum dei reverencia et honore sancte ecclesie, quia omnino de nostro
                        iure et de nostra proprietate in <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">ius
                            proprium et proprietatem </rs>sancti Eusebii Vercellensis episcopi
                        contulimus, ut omnem potestatem habeat tam Leo <placeName ref="#places/106"
                            key="#Mother_churches">Vercellensis</placeName> episcopus quam omnes sui
                        successores ita de illis predictis duabus cortibus Clauazia et Bedolio et
                        omnibus mobilibus et inmobilibus illuc respicientibus facere, sicut de aliis
                        terris quas sancta Vercellensis ecclesia pacifice et quiete tenet et tenuit.
                        Interdicimus autem ut nullus dux marchio, nullus comes, nullus vicecomes
                        nullaque imperii nostri magna aut parva persona ullam contrarietatem aut
                        minoracionem facere umquam audeat aut umquam per aliqua placita aliquo
                        ingenio fatigare. Si quis autem diabolico fastu ductus huius nostri precepti
                        violator extiterit, <rs key="#Penalty">mille libras auri</rs> obrizi componat, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">nostre
                        camere</rs> et sancto Eusebio alteram, hocque preceptum omni tempore in sua
                        permaneat firmitate. Quod ut verius credatur et in eternum conservetur, manu
                        nostra roboravimus et nostro sigillo iussimus insigniri hanc paginam. Signum
                        domni tercii Ottonis serenissimi imperatoris augusti. <persName
                            key="#Chancellor #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/3962">Heribertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> advicem<persName key="#Bishops #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/223">
                            Petri Cumani</persName> episcopi recognovit. Datum XV. kal. februarii
                        anno dominice incarnationis MI, regni vero domni tercii Ottonis XVI, imperii
                        vero V, indictione XIIII; actum autem <placeName key="#Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#places/52"></placeName>Rome in <rs key="#Palatium">palacio</rs>; feliciter amen. In
                        nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. </ab>
                </div>
